aHigher education institutions (HEIs) are increasingly affected by globalization and internationalization, with implications for language use, teaching and learning in their academic communities. As a consequence, HEIs may change their approach to multilingualism on campus, taking into account language needs as well as opportunities and challenges associated with language diversity. The book aims at discussing aspects for the design of language policies, which could support internationalization and promote multilingualism and participation of different stakeholders. By presenting a language policy model, the book provides an alternative for those engaged in language diversity in HEIs.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Jun 2024) 4aHochschulwesen. 4aInternationalisierung. 4aMehrsprachigkeit. 4aSprachenpolitik. 7aLANGUAGE ARTS & DISCIPLINES / Linguistics / General.2bisacsh  aHigher Education.  aInternationalization.  aLanguage Policies.  aMultilingualism.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDe Gruyter Mouton eBook Package 2024z97831114380470 cEPUBz97831107689300 cprintz978311076888640uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311076889340uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110768893423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783110768893/original  a978-3-11-143804-7  De Gruyter Mouton eBook Package 2024b2024  aEBA_CL_LS  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_LS  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles